item.title: Question for moparscape
item.dc:creator: @bigh51 bigh51
item.description:
@bigh51 wrote:

Hardcoding is just doing plain simple coding, instead of using things like config files or cache files.

Sir Jay:

Yeah…

Your sig is wrong. It should be:

class CommunityMember {
        public static void main(String args[]) {
			CommunityMember CM = new CommunityMember(); //We do this so the non-static void can be declared in the static main void. The class has to be declared before the variable is called to call the class.	
            System.out.println("Vote Sir Jay As A Community Member!");
            CM.SetCommunityMember();
        }	
        public void SetCommunityMember() {
        System.out.println("Sir Jay is now a Community Member.");      
       }
}

You had an undeclared string which was pointless, same with the undeclared ints.
It should be something like that, I may be wrong about the string though but that’s what I think it should be.
